description: It is difficult to place Milford Graves into a category. He is lauded as a master drummer of the 1960s avant-garde jazz scene, credited with inventing the martial arts form yara, and is established as both an herbalist and acupuncturist in New York City. Additionally, Graves is a passionate researcher of human biology and brings that knowledge to all of his work. In this conversation with Aakash Mittal filmed by Molly Sheridan, Graves talks about all of these things and shows how they are all interrelated. To read a complete transcript, please visit NewMusicBox: https://www.newmusicusa.org/milford-graves-sounding-the-universe/
title: Milford Graves: Sounding the Universe
